About Eggdrop
=============

Eggdrop was created in December 1993, making it the oldest and most
widely deployed IRC bot in existence. It evolved from a bot called
"Unrest" and has been under continuous development for over 30 years.

An IRC bot sits on channels and performs automated tasks — channel
protection, user management, flood control, logging, games, and
anything scripts can do. Eggdrop can also link multiple bots into a
botnet to share user lists, bans, and channel management across IRC
networks.

What sets Eggdrop apart is its module and scripting architecture.
Scripts can be written in Python (recommended for new installs) or
Tcl (optional). The Python API has 100% parity with the Tcl API
(239 commands). Modules extend the bot with loadable shared objects.


Requirements
------------

  - Linux, macOS, BSD, Windows (MinGW/MSVC), or Cygwin
  - C compiler with C23 support (GCC 11+, Clang 13+)
  - Meson + Ninja build system
  - At least one of: Tcl >= 8.6 or Python >= 3.8 (for scripting)
  - ~10 MB disk space

TLS 1.2/1.3 is bundled (opssl) — no external library needed. LMDB
storage is bundled in libop. IPv6 is always available.


This fork (devinkbrown)
-----------------------

This fork modernises the build system (Meson + Ninja), adds native
Windows support (IOCP), makes Tcl optional, introduces TOML
configuration, replaces unsafe C patterns with safe equivalents,
and adds a comprehensive test suite. See the README for full details.


